<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5144] JsonSlurper does not handle backslashes at the end of a String</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5144</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Whenever I try to deserialize a JSON Object with a String that ends with a correctly escaped backslash &quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot;, it throws an exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caught: groovy.json.JsonException: Expected a value on line: 1, column: 25.&lt;br/&gt;
But got an unterminated object.&lt;br/&gt;
groovy.json.JsonException: Expected a value on line: 1, column: 25.&lt;br/&gt;
But got an unterminated object.&lt;br/&gt;
	at JsonSlurperBug.run(JsonSlurperBug.groovy:9)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached a small repro.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu Linux 11.10 32-bit, &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
OpenJDK Runtime Environment (IcedTea6 1.11pre) (6b23~pre11-0ubuntu1.11.10)&lt;br/&gt;
OpenJDK Server VM (build 20.0-b11, mixed mode)</environment>
